            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, drop, bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 220°C fan. Line a large baking tray with baking paper. Whisk together the {{plain-flour}}, ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "baking powder",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa6ez3700004sv4wkk350sf"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", and {{sea-salt-fine}} in a large bowl. Rub in the cold {{unsalted-butter}} until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in the grated {{cheddar}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour in the cold {{buttermilk}} and the {{chives}}, then fold together until a rough, sticky dough just comes together. Stop as soon as there are no dry patches. Drop ten generous mounds onto the lined tray, spaced about 4 cm apart.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until the tops are deep golden and the cheese at the edges has caught and crisped. Eat warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
